cofh.api.world

Interface IFeatureGenerator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FeatureBase, FeatureGenCave, FeatureGenLargeVein, FeatureGenNormal, FeatureGenSurface, FeatureGenTopBlock, FeatureGenUnderfluid, FeatureGenUniform

    public interface IFeatureGenerator
    This interface should be implemented on classes which define a world feature to be generated in a IFeatureHandler. It is essentially a more robust version of WorldGenerator, and may include one or more WorldGenerators should you wish.

      • generateFeature

        boolean generateFeature(java.util.Random random,
                      int chunkX,
                      int chunkZ,
                      World world,
                      boolean newGen)
        Generates the world feature.
        Parameters:
        random - Random derived from the world seed.
        chunkX - Minimum X chunk-coordinate of the chunk. (x16 for block coordinate)
        chunkZ - Minimum Z chunk-coordinate of the chunk. (x16 for block coordinate)
        world - The world to generate in.
        newGen - True on initial generation, false on retrogen.
        Returns:
        True if generation happened, false otherwise.
